Gaddi, Taddeo (500115669) 'parent of' Gaddi, Giovanni di Taddeo (500057341);

He was a well-known, inventive, and influential painter who worked with Giotto but also had his own flourishing career. The first documentary evidence of Taddeo is around 1330, when he matriculated into the Arte dei Medici e Speziali. Italian painter.
Italian painter, born ca. 1300, died ca. 1366
